caption: Awesome food, very friendly staff, always great mood. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is awesome. Fantastic work.

We had the 8 course vegan brunch with sparkling rose with pomegranate juice. We got to the place 15 mins early. They open at 10:30am but Leonardo seated us even though the kitchen isn't open yet. We ordered pomegranate mimosa's instead and it was delicious. The ambiance was really well done. They have partitions that included plants for Covid-19 safety. Amazing food. I will highly suggest to try their 8 course vegan meal. We ordered 3 bottles of sparkling rose and couldn't finish the last one so we took it home.
I booked for Valentine's Day dinner with my fiance. They called to confirm me a few days before the date and told me that it was a pre-fix menu (which cost $89/person). I wasn't expecting that.
Great food. Great service.
Lovely experience.  The restraunt provided chill and classy vibes with excellent service from our waiter Georgi.  Food was spectacular with plenty of vegan and non vegan options.
Cozy atmosphere, good varied menu, delicious food and great service! Recommend!

did take out at Equinox and it was fantastic. Everything was delicious.  And since it is all take-out now, they did a great job packaging, labeling, directions for reheating. And the cocktails traveled well too.

This is a truly unique and incredible restaurant.  What a treat—indeed a gift—it is for somebody on a plant based diet to be able to enjoy a meal with the thoughtfulness, deliciousness, and creativity not often aimed at this market.  The food is superb, the presentation is beautiful, and the service (Gustavo!) is amazingly knowledgeable, friendly and accessible.  I have rarely felt for pampered, enchanted or accommodated by a restaurant.  Equinox is a treasure.

Nice upscale vegetarian option for special occasions. The menu is somewhat limited but the food (I had crispy tofu and cauliflower) was tasty. The staff was friendly and attentive. We even had a glass of champagne and wine on the house to commenrate my birthday celebration.
We had an awesome Thanksgiving dinner
Had dinner at Equinox last night.  Everything was perfect.  👍👍

Equinox gave my partner and I one of the best restaurant experiences we've ever had. It was my partners birthday and the staff went above and beyond. Alfredo and Georgie took care of us and they were attentive, kind and genuinely happy we were there. We ordered the tasting menus, my partner the plant based and mine was the market menu. Every dish was absolutely outstanding. The curried pumpkin soup was my favorite but everything was 5star quality. Will definitely return and will be talking about our evening for a while.
Very good food staff was very friendly.

Fantastic birthday brunch experience! We really liked all of the options on the brunch tasting menu, and we were able to order more of any dish we liked (at no extra cost). Juices for drinks were  fresh, everything was delicious. Staff was all very attentive. Atrium was well set up, still a really nice atmosphere. Look forward to one day getting to try the buffet brunch, but this is an excellent alternative.
One of the best birthday dinner experiences I've had in the city! Wonderful staff that went the extra mile the entire evening.
Delicious food and great service
The vegan brunch is AMAZING!  No more buffet (COVID safe), but I like the passed service even better!
Amazing food, great service, and it made for a wonderful date night.
Fantastic vegan Sunday brunch!! The staff were also wonderful.

Best take out dinner ever. I had three dishes from this week’s menu. The artichokes appetizer was a little tangy, crispy and garlicky. Delicious. I also had the salmon entree with lentils, spinach and raviolini. I love lentils and they were small and perfectly cooked. The combination of textures and flavors was amazing and well balanced. I also ordered the ratatouille because it’s a favorite of mine and it worked with the other dishes. Everything was fresh and HOT when I got it home, a ten minute walk from the restaurant. I loved my dinner and there was some of everything left over for tomorrow. I can’t wait to eat here again.

Equinox 5 course meal was absolutely amazing! Food was savory with robust flavors! I am plant based and my significant other is pescatarian, so the fact that we both were able to enjoy dinner without me having to have to just eat salads or beyond meat burgers was refreshing! Our waiter Gustavo was attentive, polite and very well informed of the entire menu!  What made the night was when Executive  Chef Todd Gray introduced himself to us and asked us how we are enjoying  the food! He was amazing, food was FAB-U-LOUS and service exceptional!!!! Will be back very soon!
Incredible vegan food. Went hwre for my 4 year anniversary absolutely NO REGRETS. The vegan cheesecake is to die for.

Had a great dinner here tonight - food and service were both on point. Love that they have multiple vegan options. Felt safe even though we were indoors. Definitely will be back - hopefully for brunch!

I’ve had my eye on Equinox for some time and was able to go a few weeks ago to celebrate a friend’s birthday. Renting the private room was a breeze however the service was just okay. This is understandable due to COVID as I’m assuming they may be understaffed. Anyhow, the gazpacho, crispy artichokes, and swordfish were delicious! I’d order them again in a heartbeat. The berry cheesecake was just okay and despite the glowing reviews, hubby said the vegan mac was not good. The top layer was the best part but the noodles were bland and didn’t have any of the stretch that Mac should have. (I know it’s vegan but I also know ingredients like tapioca starch can provide stretch). I called ahead to inquire about gluten free options and I’d estimate that about 25% of the menu was GF friendly. Unfortunately they didn’t have any gf pastas on hand so all the pasta dishes were off limits for me. Overall a good experience and I definitely want to try their brunch...once more GF items are on the menu.

Equinox was the perfect location for our small wedding reception. The room was beautifully decorated, the food was delicious, and the servers were so kind. All guests were very happy with the vegetarian and nonvegetarian options. The chocolate dessert was out of this world. Also the staff genuinely cared about our happiness. They were very accommodating, attentive, and a pleasure to be around. We thoroughly enjoyed the evening. This is the perfect venue for a memorable life event.

We went with our 18 and 20 year olds and we each loved it. There variety for vegetarians was amazing and the flavors were spot on with 80% of the food. We ordered 13 different dishes and loved it as most had different flavors and high quality ingredients. The Golden potato and sweet corn Agnolotti, Turmeric Rigatoni,  Macaroni cheese, truffles Fritters, and Tuscarora Berry Clafoutis were our favorites. We were a little disappointed in the vegetarian lasagna but not a big deal as som many items were excellent. Excellent service, social distancing and decore. Our server was very in tune to our needs and his recommendations were spot on.

My wife and I came here for our 3 year wedding anniversary; what a great choice! We were greeted at the door by Chef Todd and the kind staff. We opted for the plant-based tasting menu, which was nothing short of amazingly delicious. Our server Gustavo was very patient in explaining our menu options, and he was very sincere and genuine when checking on us and when congratulating us on our anniversary. Because of our occasion, they treated us to complimentary champagne, and even wrote us a personalized note from the staff wishing us well. This was a tasty, hospitable, and wonderful experience. Thank you to Chef Todd, Gustavo, and the entire staff for such a memorable and delicious evening!

What a wonderful experience.. took my family last nite ... Chef/owner spent so much time explaining the plant based menu items .. As well as made my son an amazing pasta dish .. The food and service was clearly a 5 star experience... and justifies the JAMES BEARD AWARDS HE SO DESERVES .. Can’t wait to visit again from NY .. best part my sons apt is a block or so away ....

This was our first time here and everything was amazing! We arrived early and we got lucky to be greeted by chef and friendly staff. Definitely a place to come back. The vegan 5 course tasting menu was top notch! Waiter was professional and knew the menu really well. Thank you so much!

We had the Sunday vegan brunch and it was great! The options were very delicious and the chef even brought us some additional sampler dish from the kitchen which was very nice. Highly recommend trying the vegan brunch! We reserved the wine room that seats 12 and the experience of dining in that room was amazing! Try the mimosas! Great variety and options!  Revisited after Covid reopening and enjoyed the delicious vegan delicacies. Wish them all the best to recover after Covid. Definitely recommend the Vegan Sunday Brunch!

This is a beautiful restaurant with a very attentive staff. The brunch is reasonably affordable.  The menu for this week was a little subpar. There were 8 courses and I liked 4 1/5 of them. The bread spread was nothing special but the gazpacho they served was delicious. The next two salad courses were also very good (a bulgar salad topped with cherries and a English cucumber and beet salad). The next three courses were a stuffed French toast rolled in granola, an "egg" frittata, and spinach pasta (as in pasta made with spinach) with pesto. I only enjoyed the French toast but with the caveat that it was definitely more just toast slices with jam in-between them. The egg frittata was very sweet and I didn't finish it. The spinach pasta was also sweet and there wasn't a hint of pesto. The last course had five desserts. I only liked the blueberry crumble. Everything else was either nothing special or just not good. Especially the fudgy brownie.  All that said, everything else about the restaurant was really good and I want to give it another try for dinner or a different brunch menu.
Absolutely fantastic vegan brunch with more courses than you can eat. Everything was delicious and well worth it.
The food was delicious and the service was excellent!
Their Plant Based menu options are superb. I loved the truffle mac especially. I can't wait to go back for vegan brunch. Gustavo was a great waiter and no detail of our meal was less than perfect.
Delicious food and the atmosphere is great. Would highly recommend!
Great food!
Unique menu and tastey
Excellent experience doing the mother's day brunch box. Delicious food, personable interaction and great value. Can't wait to go dine in person when the time is right.
They serve big portions and for affordable pricing. very kind staff. 5 stars from me.

This spot is definitely a trendy hipster kind of place! Great with friends if you want to grab some drinks and have some of their appetizers. But, I would go for the noms! I did had a bit of disappointment on the shank. It was cook to perfection! Don't get me wrong. Was just a bit on the bland side. Definitely needed something of a dip of some sorts. As for the ragu, the curry and nan, that porkbelly.... Oh man... Definitely a must try! I would come back on my next visit for sure!

I'm not vegan, but went for a friend's birthday. The staff was nice. Apparently they close at 130 but they let us stay past three to enjoy ourselves. The food was ok. There isn't allot you can do with a limited menu. On the down side, the place is very pricey, especially when you consider your only eating fruit and vegetables.

What can I say.  Horrible place. It was our 12 year anniversary.  I booked on Open Table and the menu looked great.  Once we arrived we found out they had a special menu for Feb. 15 but it was not posted on Open Table which the restaurant uses for reservations.I have seen special menus on Open Table before but I guess this restaurant was to lazy to post one. The manager with an attitude said the special menu is on their website. I told him I used Open Table. He would not make us anything that was on their normal Menu.

Great spot for vegan Sunday brunchers. We enjoyed everything. My personal favorite was the chili. The desserts were excellent. Didn't miss the eggs or milk. Brownies were so good I dare you to be able to tell they are vegan. We went for my daughter's birthday and she is vegan so we wanted something special for her and she thoroughly enjoyed herself!

Go beyond the brunch, that so many people enjoy. Dinner last night was fab. Six of us dined and each thoroughly  enjoyed several of the creative and delicious culinary creations on the menu.  Nice decor and relatively quiet dining rooms were a plus.  Our waiter was very attentive, knowledgeable and eager to please. The pace of the meal was perfect and we lingered at our leisure. After dinner we were served complementary glasses of dessert wine. Overall a great experience and we will definitely return.

Absolutely delicious— loved coming for brunch and seeing how you can take plants and elevate them to a sophisticated level— chef Todd and his team did a great job. I was blown away by the tofu scramble - super yum! - as well as the French toast! Seriously, all of it. The service is great and I loved celebrating my birthday here. We had the most amazing service at Equinox. Roman and Brett (our friends who work there) recommended it to us and completely undersold how great the experience would be. Randy, our waiter, was phenomenal. He made the experience even more fun and special with a joke for us every time he came to the table. We had multiple courses but the menu changes seasonally so we enjoyed some nice fall options like pumpkin soup. My wife was delighted by the many plant-based options and the lamb was delicious as well. The drinks had recently changed to a menu with all book titles; loved the rum diary and the catcher in the rye. Roman, Brett, and Randy(and I’m sure the rest of the staff) are truly wonderful. Literally the best treatment I have ever received at a restaurant. We will definitely be back next time we are in the area.
The service was exceptional and the food was very good. We will definitely be back

Went for a birthday celebration. We had the tasting menu and wine pairing (some of the party had the market menu, some the plant-based). All of the food was delicious, especially the pasta. The only reason for the 4 instead of 5 stars is the service- rather than move around the table to offer descriptions of the plates to our party, there was a brief word from the server at one corner of the table- in a noisy restaurant, this was not ideal. With the wine pairing, we were told what the wine (i.e. the grape varietal) was for each course, but not where it was from, nor why it was being paired with the specific courses. The wine for each coursed arrived around 5 minutes after the food, which was not optimal. All in all we had a wonderful experience.

Food was interesting but nothing tasted amazing. Just about everything needed salt added to really make it good. The service was good and the location is nice. It's possible the meat dishes are better but we only had plant based options this time.
Phenomenal food an service. Took my girlfriend and she said “this tastes like real cheese.” And she’s been looking for vegan cheese for forever. Service was great.

I have always had an amazing meal here.  As a restaurant owner in DC, I often recommend this place to customers looking for something different.  This is where my family and I go to celebrate special occasions.

*Review Specific to Sunday Brunch, though I've also come for Happy Hour and it was fantastic.*  While the price is fairly on par for DC bottomless brunches, the food is such a higher quality than any other buffet I've experienced in the city.  I came to celebrate my mother's birthday, and the staff were so sweet to us, bringing us extra dishes and birthday cake.  Would highly recommend!

Really wanted to like this place but we really didn’t. The food felt like it was right out the 90s. Most of the dishes we got were either bland or very heavy and oily… or both. Many better choices for vegan/vegetarian in the city.

Have been here many times for lunch and it was delicious. The patio is wonderful. Met s friend for happy hour last night and we sat at the bar. The HH food was not impressive.  I did not like the  pickled veggies, the risotto balls were barely warm. A cricket crawled across the placemat underneath my plate, literally in front of me. I trapped it with my napkin. The bartender scooped it up and offered my friend a free glass of wine. Odd because it was in front of me  Also, a gentleman came to sit next to me. He seemed annoyed that I couldn’t move over more, but my friend on the other side had people next to her so we little room to shift. The gentleman next to me got amazing service and few visits from the Chef. I did. It have that experience. Overall last night’s visit was disappointing. I expected more.

Great Sunday brunch - all plant-based food. Seating is all indoor but one section has great natural lighting. The brunch is buffet style & has plenty of variety - representing food from different parts of the world & savory & sweet tastes.

Everything was great except for the taste! Service, ambiance, and presentation were absolutely 5/5. But unfortunately everything we tried was so bland which is very disappointing for the price point. Had lots of shareables/apps plus main courses with a variety of plant based and not. Truffle risotto fritters had no taste of truffle. Risotto main course had very little spice/seasoning. Thought I would taste the saffron more on that dish. Not sure why the tempura vegetables were $30 - it was pretty much just fried broccoli and cauliflower over rice. Needed more sauce or a dipping sauce on the side.

Went here for my girlfriend's birthday. Lovely venue with great ambiance. The service was phenomenal. We were given great recommendations, drink pairings, etc. The swordfish steak was out of this world. Would love to come back to try the rest or the menu sometime.

Organized a set menu dinner for 30. Good news was that they accommodated us on short notice. Bad news was they changed an originally vegan soup on our set menu to add crab, didn't note it on the menu cards, and then served it to someone with a deadly shellfish allergy. Everyone survived but unlikely to return.

I went for the Sunday Vegan Brunch. While this is an amazing concept, and something I wish we had available all the time in every city,  the actual food part of the brunch was a touch underwhelming. There weren't a huge number of options (really like 7 or so) and some were incredibly simple like a salad, plain pancakes, and grilled asparagus. The real stars of the show were the pineapple gazpacho (I would literally swim in a pool of that it was so tasty and very complex with the mint and cucumber), the walnut French toast rhubarb sandwiches, and the dessert table (SO good). Everything else was just alright and not really moving. Mostly just simple food that is already easily vegan at normal restaurants and wasn't quite as hot as it should have been. The staff though was absolutely excellent and really so kind throughout the whole brunch.  Would I go again? Probably not for the $52 it ended up costing with a coffee (why is this an extra $5 again???), tax, and tip but it wasn't a bad experience at all, just simple for the price.

This is a gem! Outstanding food and service. Their menu changes frequently, farm to table approach, many amazing meat and vegetarian options. This was one of my highlights in DC and will absolutely be back! Great staff that recommended the nicest dishes and went out of their way to make my experience awesome. And the ribs were out of this world ... 6 stars!
Truely Five Star experience.
A Very nice quiet intimate restaurant with an extraordinary menu...A very special place.

Eqinox is amazing. I love that they have a full vegan menu. Their high prices are well worth the quality of their restaurant, service, and food. And the food... Words can't even describe how delicious their food is. And the fact that they are trying to also impact the amount of food wasted in the restaurant industry is amazing. My family and I attended their Not Wasted dinner, a dinner created around the movement of not wasting as much food in the restaurant industry, and in general, and on educating the attendees about the amount of food wasted in households, but also in the restaurant industry, and why we should care about it, and how it affects the environment as well as the ecosystem. And the dinner they served attendees, BEYOND delicious. And it was made from things you normally would have thrown away, like carrot shavings, lettuce stems, etc. The menu they created for that night was delicious. They had another Not Wasted dinner yesterday, 04/22, to celebrate Earth Day (even though I'm sure they all acknowledge the fact that every day is Earth Day) and I wish I could have attended. But the menu looked just as delicious as their initial Not Wasted dinner menu, and their regular, seasonal menus that they have. In general the restaurant has amazing food. The photos included are from their main menu as well as their first Not Wasted dinner in February. This is one restaurant I highly recommend trying out. Chef Todd Gray and his wife Ellen have created an amazing restaurant and amazing environment for their guests to eat in, as well as an amazingly tasty vegan menu that I recommend everyone try!
Very tasty, no complaints. If I could make a request, please bring back the tofu scramble

Very nice selection of food and drinks. The menu is half vegetarian/vegan and half contain meat. The staff was great and worked together to ensure comfort throughout the whole dining process.
The service was as excellent as the food and much friendlier than one would expect in downtown DC!

Equinox’s vegan brunch was recommended to me by a childhood friend, who drives there with his wife from Maryland, to partake in their fantastic fare. I planned a brunch with girlfriends for my birthday, but the first snowstorm of the year cut my guest list down to just one other person. Ellen of Equinox asked if we could visit earlier to allow for their staff to make it home safely. What caring consideration!!! My friend and I (over)indulged to our healthy hearts’ content as Roman, our waiter, provided excellent service. The head chef/owner stopped by to chat with us as well. AND they had a little birthday treat for me! I’m still having lip puckering visions of the lemon squares from their pastry table. I look forward to visiting Equinox again. Truly fine dining with ethics and a desire to reduce their footprint on this fragile planet.
Portions were small and overdone. Seemed like leftovers. Arrogant staff!

Lovely selection of vegan and gluten free options at Sunday brunch. Incredible staff, both kitchen and front of house. The nurse thanks you for the Bloody Mary's and hopes the bartender is healing well!
Went to the vegan brunch on Sunday had some pancakes, brussel sprouts with cauliflower, bok choy is a delicious sauce.  Left this place completely stuffed and satisfied worth every penny
Absolutely loved this place. The staff was polite and professional. The mimosas were delicious and the food was like no other, flavorful, fresh and what a variety to choose from.

I came for restaurant week, but I would recommend the restaurant overall for anyone who is looking to have something healthy and local while also spending a little more. The food is delicious and the portions are just right. The restaurant has multiple dining rooms, one of which was in a sunroom-type area where we were able to watch the snow fall while enjoying a business meal.
Celebrated a birthday here - food and service was excellent! They also bake birthday cakes on request which was very handy
Absolutely delicious cauliflower soup and rockfish entree. We had a show to catch and everyone made sure we were served in time. I can't wait to go back!

Valentine's menu was wonderful. It was incredible to have a fine dining plant based meal. We had a chance to meet chef Todd Gray and we love what he and his wife Ellen are doing to encourage plant based food and sustainability in the restaurant world.

My Equinox Experience The best plant based fine dining restaurant in DC. Excellent dining experience for a non-vegan like myself. Fine Dining ✅ Excellent Food✅ Fine Wine✅ Friendly and courteous staff ✅ Food Presentation ✅ Good Service ✅ Lovely Ambiance ✅ Highly Recommend

Been here a number of times over the past 20 years. Had not been for a year or two and i wonder why we have not put Equinox in our regular rotation. Great service, comfortable seating, a nice hum to the room. And the food and wine were great. The rack or pork was legendary. We will be back...soon.

We had dinner at Equinox Tuesday night. It was not busy. We were seated right away. They have a few tables outside. We were treated with a complementary appetizer: slices of a fig with a few veggies on top. Not sure it is a gerular menu item. The menu is not overwhelmingly long but there is a choice of everything: vegetarian, fish, chicken, beef, and lamb. We ordered an appetizer: grilled octopus which they split into two plates for us to share. Great size portion and great presentation! Cooked just right and set on top of some veggies. I ordered a vegetarian mushroom dish and my companion ordered fish. Both dishes came in a timely manner. Food was hot and well prepared. Nice presentation! Good size portions. We were very happy with food quality! I didn't find the desert list very interesting but they have a good selection on hot teas. The desert we ordered was just ok. But we are usually not into deserts. Service was great! Our server was attentive but not overwhelming hanging over our shoulders. The atmosphere is very pleasant and it was not very noisy outside after 8 pm. Pleasant experience overall!

With all the new restaurants opening every year it's often too easy to forget about some of the classics. Equinox seems like it has been around forever. My lunch of the rockfish special and the Yule log desert was tasty, served nicely in this white tablecloth restaurant 3 blocks from the White House, but way overpriced for the value of the experience. The waiter first described the special as a large filet of rockfish; I was served what appeared to be exactly 4 ounces. Beautifully cooked and presented on a bed of halved brussel sprouts and other veggies, but still basically a 3 inch square piece of fish, see photo. When asked the price of the special the waiter first said it was probably the same as the other fish dishes on the menu, in the low 20 dollar range. And it would have been fine at that price, but no, it was $10 more. The waiter had no idea of what the Yule log was. However it proved tasty enough, although the accompanying chestnut gelato was the highlight of the meal, see photo. Interesting experience but I see no reason to return.

I am a vegetarian so I loved having Equinox as an option in the business lunch scene dominated by steakhouses, but it pains me to say I will not be coming back. Average entree is $20-ish for lunch. I ordered the special, a vegetarian pasta with brussel sprout leaves, parmesan and truffle oil. Get the check, it's $56. I balk and ask why on earth if a special is three times the price of every other pasta on the menu, they would not say so. Waiter says no one ever asks (BECAUSE YOU SHOULD VOLUNTEER THAT HIGHLY COUNTER-INTUITIVE INFORMATION) and said he would discount the price. It was discounted $8 to the appetizer portion. He tells me white truffle is thousands of dollars and people don't always know that. That is obnoxious, and a reason why you should say the price. I guess it's expensive but I don't know how much and shouldn't be expected to factor that in. This is not an "obvious" luxury item like filet mignon with a side of foie gras. You can get truffle mac or truffle fries at your neighborhood Olive Garden. Also, I didn't love the "special" and thought it was oily. I have eaten here before and had a good experience, but this was unbelievable. You cannot just scam customers this way just because you typically have a business crowd. Concealing information from your customers is not a way to show how "upscale" you are, it is downright dishonest. You lost a repeat customer.  ***EDITED: The managers were very persistent in calling me back and apologizing for the situation and have offered to comp the price of a future meal. I was happy to hear they have implemented a policy chance and now print the special, along with the price, on the menu (which is really the only fix I was interested in). Raising to 3-stars because I appreciate them implementing a change.
